What a year we look back on, what a year we look forward to.
_
Wishing everyone who sees this a merry Christmas and happy New Year. I will be spending the last week of this year with my family and friends. That’s why I don’t wanna be on my phone during this time and will therefore be #offline for the next few days. @flowsofly will be back in 2020 with art, poetry and love. Thank you for following my flow ♡

„My young one has a chronic auto-immune disease. We worked on her health for 5 years in which I didn’t sleep, did medical studies on Google and tried to do everything to help her. Now she can finally live a somewhat normal life. My two girls are the only family I’ve got. And I feel that I always have to be strong for them. Sometimes I feel like a rock who must stay firm, one who must never fall over, no matter how swamped I am. A family portrait which reflects this emotion, this close bond and love, would mean the world to me.. to remember to be strong and never fall down. You know, if people knew what it’s like to have kids.. who knows how many would still get one.. it’s like carrying your own heart outside of your body. Completely unprotected and exposed. And if something happens to them or they feel bad, you almost die from it. You must be strong for them.“
— the touching story from a single-mother creative from Austria who commissioned this last artwork I worked on this year (130x90cm marker on canvas)
Alright, bring your best Christmas pun!

Tell me about all the things you wanna do together.

Tiptoe if you must, but make the step. I started making a drawing a day in 2015 and look where that has taken me.
This year I quit my office job to focus on art full-time. Your support and appreciation has been enormous and I want to thank you dearly for following my flow. I was invited to do exhibitions in Austria, Italy, USA and Peru this year and seeing so many of you interact with my art IRL warmed my heart, brought tears to my eyes and makes me very excited for everything that’s to come in 2020!
With this I also want to encourage you to reflect on your 2019 and choose some activities that make you smile. Find ways of how you can do more of them starting today. Some people believe in new year’s resolutions but I feel that positive change can happen anytime if you only want.
A friend recently shared this line: „everything you don’t change, you choose“ which has stuck with me and keeps motivating me to edit my life. It’s the only one we got. And one day it will be over. Let’s enjoy it, live with passion, kindness and courage and turn it into a masterpiece.
Be-you-tiful

I titled this one „Love chess“ and when she asked what it means I replied that love‘s really a game you play together but some play against each other.

#Vienna: tomorrow Wednesday evening there is an opportunity to acquire works from my exhibition (and additional ones I made in 50x70cm), please message me for details if you’re interested. Time: 17:30-18:30, Prices from €400.

Vienna, wow! Thank you! 🥰 You’ve warmed my heart so dearly with your numerous presence and kind feedback. We made timeslots for the exhibition to allow everyone an intimate experience and they were all pretty much sold out. 😳 People drove here for hours, took planes, trains and buses to experience this show I put together. I am truly overwhelmed. With this social media thing it’s easy to get caught up in large numbers but this weekend showed how real this hype is. You are real! Unreal in your presence and kindness. ♡
Thank you @einflussraum.at for helping me create this experience, for letting me write and draw on every surface and drill holes where we needed them. You’re amazing hosts. A special thank you also to the followers who lent their voices to the exhibition, recorded my texts and made this an experience for multiple senses. And finally to @nickycube for the live tattooing on the opening night. Everything worked out! Even our gift shop with the last @franzvondurst gin bottles, special Christmas print cards and exhibition tote bags sold out. 🤯🥳
I am SO excited for 2020. 🤩 You guys have messaged me to come to essentially every city on this planet and I will try my best to put together some mesmerizing shows next year. 🙌 Thank you for allowing me to do this. Falling asleep extra inspired, humbled and grateful today. Thank you! Much love! 💛
Falling in love with another woman helped me to compare myself less to other women and appreciate our beautiful individuality more.

Yesterday Abby traveled for 14 hours to my exhibition opening to claim her raffle prize: a @flowsofly tattoo by @nickycube in Vienna. What an amazing opening night, thank you Abby, thank you Nicky, thank you @einflussraum.at for hosting this and thank you everyone for letting me make art and for celebrating love and intimacy.
The Vienna show is on this weekend until Sunday.

#Vienna: With this show I wanted to go beyond putting art on the walls. Therefore I’ve conceived an experience for you, a Kopfkino as we say in German, a walk-through movie told in artworks with subtitles and voices by some brave local followers. I’m deeply thankful to everyone for making this possible and can’t wait to welcome you. Opening tomorrow Thursday and running until Sunday. 😍😍

Why, why was I so afraid to admit
That all I really wanted was to commit
To quit that nightly nomad shit
And deep long kiss my perfect fit

Learning to forgive, accept, appreciate and love myself meant closing my eyes to feel what only I could feel and opening my eyes to see what only I could see. It meant losing the norms and expectations they had (whoever “they” were) and replacing them with my own standards, goals and recipes for smiles. It meant saying no to a lot of things and being okay with not being everyone’s darling or bitch. It also meant saying yes to a lot of things that I truly wanted and valued and being okay with following an unconventional path of love and art.
_
#selfcare #selflove #illustration #tattooart #lineart #linearttattoo
